Select sprite (24)
#Parent OS_SpriteOp_Reason
=>	R0 =	<24, &18=>os_spriteop_reason2> (Select sprite)
	R1 =	<Sprite area=>os_spriteop_area>
	R2 =	Sprite name/pointer
<=	R2 =	Address/Offset of sprite unless in wimp or system area.

This SWI is meant for selecting the given sprite for subsequent plotting with VDU 25,232-239. This usage is not recommended, but the side effect of returning the address is more useful.
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 775=>PRM-1:775>
